THE CITY OF LEESBURG, FLORIDA, a municipal corporation, v. CERTAIN LANDS upon which Taxes or Special Assessments, or Both, are Delinquent; the STATE OF FLORIDA, et al. 21 So. (2nd) 42

January Term, 1945

February 27, 1945 Division A P. C. Gorman and Rr P. Hamlin, for appellant. Walter Warren, for appellees. PER CURIAM:

The record and the briefs in this case have been examined and we find no reversible error.

Affirmed.

CHAPMAN, C. J., TERRELL, BUFORD and ADAMS, JJ., concur.
